{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὑφαιρ-έω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> -ήσω (ὑφελῶ in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aquila LXX.Exo.5.19): \">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]<i>aorist</i> ὑφεῖλον (<i>aorist 1</i> <i>middle</i> ὑφειλάμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Job.21.18)\">LXX</a>]: <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>ὑπαιρέω</b>, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.65, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>serze underneath</b> or <b>inwardly,</b> τοὺς δ᾽ ἄρ᾽ ὑπὸ τρόμος εἷλεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.862, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.450. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>draw</b> or <b>take away from under,</b> ὑπὸ δ᾽ ᾕρεον ἕρματα νηῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.154; ἄνθεμον ποντίας ἐέρσας 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 7.79 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; [τὸ παιδίον τῆς μητρός] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 161a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὴν χεῖρα ὑφῄρει <b>tried to draw</b> it <b>away,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 689. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>take away underhand, filch away,</b> [τῶν Ἀθηναίων] τοὺς ξυμμάχους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.13 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὑ. τὴν πρόσοδον, τὴν εὐπορίαν, <b>diminish</b> it <b>gradually,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 31, 82 \">Refs</a>]; <b>purloin, steal,</b> βοῦν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PSI” 4.366.2 (3rd c.BC); ταῦτα (i.e. ζεῦγος χεροψελίων κτλ.) [prev. work] 10.1128.30 (3rd c.AD) \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; of a doctor, ὑ. τὸ οἰνάριον καὶ τὸ λουτρόν <b>remove</b> from the regime, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 2.15 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ὑ. τῆς ὑποψίας <b>gradually to take away</b> part of.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.42; so ὑ. τοῦ πλήθεος 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀρχαίης ἰητρικῇς” 5; τοῦ τόνου 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Philops.” 8; τῆς ὀργῆς 3rd-2nd c.BC: Phalaris Epistolographus “Epistulae - Epistolographi” 72 codices (ὑφῆκα Valckenaer)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, ὑφῃρέθη σου, κάλαμος ὡσπερεὶ λύρας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 36; ὑπαραιρημένος \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>put secretly away, made away with,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.65 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—also <i>middle</i>, <b>filch, purloin,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 745, “Nu.” 179, “Pl.” 1140, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 45.58, “PCair.Zen.” 350.4 (3rd c.BC), etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὑ. τοὺς καιροὺς τῆς πόλεως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.66; τὴν δημοκρατίαν ἄρδην ὑ. [prev. work]145; ὑ. τί τινος\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <b>filch</b> it <b>from</b> him, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.83, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 14.37, etc.; χρήματα ἐξ Ἐλαιοῦντος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.116; ὑ. μοῦ τὴν ἀπολογίαν 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “pro Lycophrone” 11; ὑ. τι ἐξ ἱερῶν ἢ ὁσίων 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 857b: _absolutely_, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 556. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <i>middle</i> also with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i>, ὑ. τινά τινος <b>rob</b> him of.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.222 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; σιγῇ τοῦθ᾽ ὑφαιρούμεσθά νιν <b>keep</b> it <b>from</b> him.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 271. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>subtract, deduct,</b> ὑφαιρεθέντος τοῦ ἐπιδεκάτου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 42(1).103.325, +others (Epid., 4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὑφαιρουμένης τῆς προικὸς τῆς προδεδομένης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 1102.10 (2nd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9606","accentedUnicode":"ὑφαιρέω","shortDef":"to take up","mediumDef":"to take up","stepGloss":"to take up","stepTransliteration":"hufaireō","_step_Type":"verb"}]}